# Implementation Plan - IntradayScreener Bot & UI

## Goal
Transform the standalone Python bot into a Web Application. The Backend (FastAPI) will run on Render and handle the trading logic. The Frontend (Next.js) will run on Vercel and display specific Sector and Signal data.

## User Review Required
- **Deployment**: User handles pushing to Render/Vercel. I provided the code and config.
- **Backend URL**: The Frontend will need the deployed Render URL to fetch data. I will set a placeholder `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` in `.env.local`.

## Components

### 1. Backend (Python/FastAPI)
- **`api.py`**: New entry point.
    -   Running [main.py](file:///C:/Users/Ashbin/.gemini/antigravity/brain/2df2ed12-f98d-4c89-bf98-dea5fc2acbc3/main.py) logic in a `threading.Thread` or `asyncio.create_task` on startup.
    -   **State Management**: `BOT_STATE` dictionary to store:
        -   `top_sectors`: List of current top 2 sectors.
        -   `signals`: List of generated buy signals (Symbol, Time, Price).
    -   **Endpoints**:
        -   `GET /`: Health check.
        -   `GET /data`: Returns `BOT_STATE`.
- **Refactoring**: Modify [main.py](file:///C:/Users/Ashbin/.gemini/antigravity/brain/2df2ed12-f98d-4c89-bf98-dea5fc2acbc3/main.py) 's loop to update a shared state object instead of just printing.

### 2. Frontend (Next.js - Vercel)
- **Tech**: Next.js 14 (App Router), Tailwind CSS (Premium Design).
- **Pages**:
    -   `Dashboard`:
        -   **Sectors Card**: Visual bars showing NIFTY_IT % change etc.
        -   **Signals Feed**: Live-updating list of buy signals.
        -   **Status Indicator**: "Bot Running" / "Market Closed".
- **Design**: Dark mode, glassmorphism, green/red accents for market data.

